docs.abstract: An Ohio congressional special election has revealed the strategy Republicans will use to keep power in the House — or to ensure that Democrats win only a small majority.
docs.snippet: An Ohio congressional special election has revealed the strategy Republicans will use to keep power in the House — or to ensure that Democrats win only a small majority.
docs.lead_paragraph: DUBLIN, Ohio — Republicans everywhere are confronting an ominous political environment, a Democratic opposition rippling with energy and a president on their own side who is prone to divisive outbursts and policy decrees.

headline.main: In Ohio Election, Republicans Test a Midterm Rescue Plan: Polarization
headline.print_headline: Scrambling to Preserve House Edge, G.O.P. Pushes Polarization

docs.abstract: Mr. Buttigieg said Thursday that he had not understood at the time that the phrase had become a sort of counter-slogan to the Black Lives Matter movement.
docs.snippet: Mr. Buttigieg said Thursday that he had not understood at the time that the phrase had become a sort of counter-slogan to the Black Lives Matter movement.
docs.lead_paragraph: It was March 2015, and Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., recognized that the country was having what he called a “painful dialogue” about how people of color and law enforcement were coexisting in their communities. The Black Lives Matter movement was growing in influence after several high-profile killings of black men by police officers.

headline.main: Pete Buttigieg Faces Scrutiny Over ‘All Lives Matter’ Remark in 2015
headline.print_headline: Three Words From 2015  Scrutinized  In 2020 Bid

docs.abstract: Though Senator Dianne Feinstein trounced Kevin de León in a primary, they will still face off in November, after party leaders endorsed Mr. de León, reflecting the power of liberal activists.
docs.snippet: Though Senator Dianne Feinstein trounced Kevin de León in a primary, they will still face off in November, after party leaders endorsed Mr. de León, reflecting the power of liberal activists.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The first rebuke to Senator Dianne Feinstein came in February, when the California Democratic Party delivered 54 percent of its convention vote to her opponent, Kevin de León, a state senator — just short of the 60 percent he needed for the party’s endorsement.

headline.main: Feinstein Has Advantages in California Race. De León Now Has Party Leaders.

docs.abstract: Fifty years ago this month, Catholic activists dragged draft files into a Maryland parking lot and incinerated them.
docs.snippet: Fifty years ago this month, Catholic activists dragged draft files into a Maryland parking lot and incinerated them.
docs.lead_paragraph: They entered the draft board office near Baltimore in broad daylight and ransacked the drawers, seizing hundreds of papers as a clerk tried to wrest them back. Outside, in front of journalists they had summoned, they dumped the files of would-be soldiers in the parking lot and incinerated them with a napalm-like mixture made from gasoline and Ivory soap.

headline.main: Their Protest Helped End the Draft. 50 Years Later, It’s Still Controversial.

docs.abstract: He narrowly beat the first-day haul of Senator Bernie Sanders, who raised $5.9 million after announcing his bid last month and who would go on to raise $10 million before his first week was over.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Beto O’Rourke raised more than $6 million online in the first 24 hours after announcing his presidential campaign last week, according to his campaign, outpacing his rivals for the Democratic nomination and making an emphatic statement about his grass-roots financial strength.

headline.main: Beto O’Rourke Raised $6.1 Million Online in First 24 Hours of Campaign
headline.print_headline: With $6.1 Million in First 24 Hours, O’Rourke Bursts Out of the Fund-Raising Gate

docs.abstract: On Monday night, the two major candidates for governor in Ohio, a critical swing state, met to debate. Two New York Times political reporters attended, and afterward assessed the proceedings.
docs.snippet: On Monday night, the two major candidates for governor in Ohio, a critical swing state, met to debate. Two New York Times political reporters attended, and afterward assessed the proceedings.
docs.lead_paragraph: ALEX: Sydney, that gubernatorial debate we just watched was, to borrow a line, a thrilla in vanilla. It’s almost refreshing to see two very conventional, polite men debate like that. Are we on a different planet?

headline.main: In Ohio Governor’s Debate, Wonky Candidates in a Divided State

docs.abstract: The Hawaii Senator has gained newfound prominence as a leading Democratic voice calling for Judge Kavanaugh’s accusers to be heard and respected.
docs.snippet: The Hawaii Senator has gained newfound prominence as a leading Democratic voice calling for Judge Kavanaugh’s accusers to be heard and respected.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Mazie Hirono of Hawaii has made national headlines in the last week with her blunt comments about the treatment of women and the sexual assault allegations against Judge Brett Kavanaugh. At a recent news conference, for instance, she urged men to “shut up and step up,” and she told Senator Mitch McConnell, the majority leader, to “do the right thing” as he passed her in a Capitol Hill hallway.

headline.main: ‘I Believe Her’: Mazie Hirono Takes an Aggressive Stance in Kavanaugh Hearings

docs.abstract: Democrats and Republicans alike believe that when Georgia chooses between Stacey Abrams and Brian Kemp, they will be signaling what the Deep South powerhouse stands for.
docs.snippet: Democrats and Republicans alike believe that when Georgia chooses between Stacey Abrams and Brian Kemp, they will be signaling what the Deep South powerhouse stands for.
docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — The Republican won the nomination Tuesday after branding himself a politically incorrect conservative who would “round up criminal illegals” and haul them to the border in his very own pickup. The Democrat all but opened her campaign by demanding that the iconic carvings of Jefferson Davis, Robert E. Lee and Stonewall Jackson be sandblasted off Stone Mountain.

headline.main: In Georgia Governor’s Race, a Defining Moment for a Southern State
headline.print_headline: Political Middle Is All but Ignored In Georgia Race

docs.abstract: Mr. Booker, of New Jersey, is one of several potential Democratic presidential candidates who is crisscrossing the country, getting themselves in front of voters.
docs.snippet: Mr. Booker, of New Jersey, is one of several potential Democratic presidential candidates who is crisscrossing the country, getting themselves in front of voters.
docs.lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey did not announce he was running for president on Saturday. Nor did he say he was thinking about it. But on a demoralizing day for Democrats, he came to this bellwether state and sounded a lot like someone who wanted to lead the Democratic Party in its quest to oust President Trump from the White House.

headline.main: Cory Booker Criticizes Trump in Iowa, Where Presidential Hopefuls Flock
headline.print_headline: New Jersey Senator, In Iowa Visit, Appears To Test 2020 Waters
